==English==

===Verb===
#Variant of the simple past and past participle of [[shit]].

===Adjective===
#Of or pertaining to the quality of excrement. 

''Before God, master fool, if you do not let me alone, or that you will presume to vex me any more, you shall receive from the best hand I have a mask wherewith to cover your rascally scroundrel face, you paltry '''shitten''' [[varlet]]''. --Francois Rabelais, ''Gargantua and Pantagruel'' [http://www.fullbooks.com/Gargantua-and-Pantagruel-Complete-8.html (translated from French)]. The word has also been used when translating [[The Frogs]] of [[Aristophanes]], describing the lake [[Herakles]] traversed to get to [[Hades]] anterior to his [[harrowing of hell]]